	Mobile Fingerprint
	South Australia Police has implemented a mobile fingerprint scanning solution that allows officers to verify a person’s identity on the go. The solution, deployed by NEC, gives officers access to the National Police Reference System (NPRS) of CrimTrac, the national information-sharing service for Australian’s police, law enforcement and national security agencies
	Instead of verifying a person's identity with fingerprint scanning technology at the station, SAPOL officers equipped with NEC’s mobile solution can now independently do this when the person is present at the scene of a crime or during other questioning, such as missing persons investigations. The technology will reduce police officers’ vulnerability to inaccurate identity claims. Name, verhicle and registration checks possible
