	ETS2 Travel Management
	ETS2 (cloud based) helps the gov to further consolidate online travel booking services and expense management platforms and channels, driving additional cost savings and efficiencies while delivering a transparent service for improved accountability, increase transparency and reduced waste. Background: The U.S. Fed Gov is the largest consumer of travel services in the world, with an estimated $15 billion in annual spend. The first generation of ETS unified over 80 Executive Branch agencies to a common, secure, web-based, automated service. It consolidated over 250 disparate, non-web-based and paper-driven systems; leveraged the government’s purchasing power; increased online adoption from 5 to 68%; saving millions annually and reducing reimbursement cycle time.
	 ETS2 serves as the gateway to optimize the government’s scale and full market leverage to lower travel costs.
-Improved usability and optimized online travel planning;
-Increased navigation and ease-of-use, enabling informed cost and sustainability decisions at point-of-sale; and
-Strengthened operational environment, improving management by adopting commercial best practices in software development, data transparency and improved security controls.
	http://www.gsa.gov/portal/content/104378 
