(Agricultural Marketing Systems Development Program) 
	Commodity price service by SMS, The project’s objective is to increase rural poor people’s food security and incomes by improving the structure and performance of the marketing system.The target group of AMSDP: smallholder farmers as well as producers groups and other grassroots institutions. The programme aims to promote interactions between them and the small-scale traders’ and processors’ groups operating in the rural areas. The targeted districts are those that have productive and marketing potential, favorable agro -ecological conditions and organized producers’ groups. Activities are designed to improve the bargaining position of the producer s’ groups within the marketplace by strengthening their capacity to identify market opportunities and negotiate prices. 
