	Nachtrag zu: 
LEA goes Mobile
	Ein flotter Slogan für die Dienste des Landeseinwohneramtes (LEA) zeigt erste  Schritte auf, Verwaltungsdienste zu vereinfachen. Die Anwendung soll einen  mobilen Zugriff auf das Melderegister des Landeseinwohneramts Berlin ermöglichen. Vor allem soll der elektronische Vorgang Zeit und Personal bei Behörden & Kunden einsparen. Per mobilem Endgerät wird eine Meldeanfrage an die Behörde gesandt (Name,  Vorname, Geburtsdatum). Bei positivem Ergebnis wird die Adresse des Angefragten übermittelt. Es gab bereits schon erste erfolgreiche Pilotversuche. Die tatsächliche Umsetzung erfordert allerdings eine technisch sichere Abwicklung und sollte auf die in diesem Bereich bestehenden Standards OSCI und XMeld aufbauen. Hierbei bestehen noch Hindernisse, da OSCI noch nicht für mobile Endgeräte umgesetzt worden ist. Außerdem wurde für die wirtschaftliche Nutzung, v.a. die  Potenziale der Abrechnung, noch nicht geklärt. Die Pilotversion wurde ersatzweise über einen OSCI-Proxy realisiert und wurde  nur begrenzt den notwendigen Sicherheitsstandards gerecht. Bevor die genannten Hindernisse nicht überwunden sind, ist mit einer endgültigen Realisierung  nicht zu rechnen. Immerhin wird an der Einführung einer flächendeckenden, digitalen Signatur in der Verwaltung derzeit gearbeitet, mit deren Einführung frühestens 2005 zu  rechnen ist.
. 
	G2B, G2G: Zielgruppe sind diesmal nicht der Bürger, sondern in erster Linie Transportunternehmen (G2B) und die Polizei (G2G), die von einer schnelleren  Identitätsüberprüfung profitieren sollen. 
Die Idee wurde offenbar nicht realisiert
	http://www.m-government.info/files/Mobile-Government_booklet-print.pdf
S. 39
 
	

	

	GER
	2
	Weiterbildung Mitarbeiter in der Cloud
	Cloudbasiertes Training. Laut Materna besteht die Lösung aus einem Learning-Management-System, unterstützt den Einsatz virtueller Klassenräume und liefert virtuelle Trainingsinfrastrukturen. Ebenfalls neu ist die Schulung zu Sicherheitsfragen. Mithilfe der Training Suite könnten Organisationen selbst die größte Anzahl an Mitarbeitern in kurzer Zeit für das Thema IT-Sicherheit sensibilisieren. 
	G2G, G2B
Dadurch sind Schulungen orts- und endgerätunabhängig durchführbar und lassen sich flexibel an die jeweilige Anwenderanzahl anpassen. Weiterbildung aus der Cloud ist insgesamt flexibler, schneller realisierbar und effizienter.
	http://www.kommune21.de/meldung_18353_Weiterbildung+in+der+Cloud.html


	Materna,
http://www.materna.de/DE/Loesungen/ServicesUndInfrastrukturenSchaffen/MaternaTrainingSuite/MaternaTrainingSuite_node.html


Neuvorstellung CeBIT 2014
	

	GER
	3
	Collection to citizens
	Identification and differentiation of fundamental components concerning mGov services 
	

	

	

	

	

		3.1.
	SMS alerts for public safety


	warnings on storms, bushfires, floods, bomb threats: crisis information and instructions. In Hong Kong SMS messages are used to target people with hearing difficulties who cannot hear audible warnings for floods and typhoons.
	

	

	

	

		3.2.
	Location-based services
	such as tourism information, advice of health facilities in an area, weather or transport information


	specifics: see No. 5
	

	

	

		3.3.
	School Applications
	no-show alerts to parents of school students to reduce truancy, SMS messages regarding school field trips or return of consent forms.
	

	

	

	

		3.4.
	Authentication Applications
	use of mobile phones as an authentication mechanism (rather than a smart card for example), to enable access to government services
	

	

	

	

		3.5.
	Health applications
	particularly SMS messages to remind patients to take medicines and attend appointments. This is a service currently provided by BreastscreenWA. 
	specifics: see No. 6
	

	

	

		3.6.
	Direct Citizen Interaction
	SMS collection of citizen complaints, feedback, input to public issues
	

	

	

	

		3.7.
	Personalized SMS alerts
	including: Library Books Due, Notification on Upcoming Parliament Sitting, Passport Renewal, License Renewal, Parking Offences, and Season Parking.
	

	

	

	

		3.8.
	Pay Bills and Fines
	including traffic infringements, Land Tax, Payroll Tax etc.
	specifics: see No. 7
	

	

	

		3.9.
	Missing Persons Alerts
	in Europe photographs of missing persons are sent to taxi drivers and bus drivers immediately the person is registered as missing.
	

	

	

	

		3.10.
	Tax verification
	prefilled tax forms are sent to citizens’ mobile devices where on receipt they verify the details as being correct and confirm via an SMS message.
	

	

	

	

	4
	Collection: Potential field staff applications 
	

	

	

	

	

	

		4.1.
	Moving Images
	video conferencing and information sharing. This will decrease the potential for isolation and will increase staff’ ability to collaborate while in the field.
	* Fortbildung, see No. 2
* 	

	

	

		4.2.
	File Transfer
	pushing files to office for submission while in the field. This will increase staff’ efficiency, reduce workload and delays in the submission of reports.
	

	

	

	

		4.3.
	Collaborative Working
	staff are able to communicate in real time while in the field on difficult issues and interact with other employees.
	

	

	

	

		4.4.
	Electronic Staff
	there is the potential for some staff to work electronically from different field locations in order to service remote and rural communities as well as metropolitan areas without the need for a physical presence.
	

	

	

	

		4.5.
	Job Dispatch
	urgent cases and new jobs can be dispatched while staff are away from the office. Information can also be forwarded to ensure staff are informed and updated on new developments.
	

	

	

	

		4.6.
	Remote Monitoring and instant messaging
	central office management remain connected to field staff at all times. This not only increases the ability of the agency to monitor its staff but also increases the safety of the staff in the field.


	

	

	

	

		4.7.
	Field inspection
	maintenance of government assets, with automatic upload to a central database. 
	

	

	

	

		4.8.
	Vehicle Positioning
	allows central offices to remain in contact with staff and also allows them to ensure that they know the whereabouts of their staff. This will increase the safety level of field staff and reduce the risk of staff experiencing duress and the central office not being aware of their location. It is also useful during the transportation of dangerous goods.
	

	

	

	

	5
	Location-based Services (LBS)








	Potential, Examples and Ideas:
LBS are transforming the ways people across the country conduct business, organize their lives, and have fun. They can save time, money, and even lives. However, because of the technologies that enable them, LBS have the inherent ability to create accurate snapshots of their users’ activities that can contain very personal information. The potential of LBS to provide value and foster innovation to benefit the economy and consumers is tremendous. It is clear that there are also threats to consumers’ legitimate interest in protecting their personally identifiable information, in particular from the lack of clear and consistent disclosure about how that information is being collected, safeguarded and used by location-based services.


	Location based services: 
* Industry, 
* Government, 
* Business, 
* Health
z.B. Freiwilligendienste
	Beispiele? Ideen?
e.g. 
* Microsoft: CityNext
   * http://www.microsoft.com/government/ww/public-services/city-next/Pages/about.aspx




	

	

	

		5.1.
	Citizen
	Navigation and Travel – Applications in this category allow a user to perform a search based in part on location, i.e., to find the nearest hotel, ATM, bus stop, or particular restaurant. 


	Examples: WHERE, Yelp, Zagat, MapQuest 4Mobile, Google Places, Yellow Pages Mobile, NextBus, OpenTable, and Star Walk


	

	

	

	

	5.2.
	Citizen
	Tracking and Geosocial Networking– Using applications in this category, users can share their location with friends, family, or strangers via online social networks. Included in this category are applications that recommend restaurants or other places of interest based on where a user’s network of “friends” has checked-in, or that enables businesses to reward their customers for loyalty based on repeated visits or check-ins. Other applications in this category enable parents to track the location of their children, family and caregivers to monitor dementia patients, and pet owners to recover lost dogs.
	Examples of tracking and social location “check-in” applications include FourSquare, Loopt, Family Locator, Adient, Tagg, FindFriends, Gowalla, Facebook Places, Twitter, and Yelp.


	

	

	

	

	5.3.
	Citizen


	Gaming and Entertainment – These applications allow users to play games on their wireless devices with friends and family, persons in their local network, or anyone online. Some location-based games track phone movement and create real-life scavenger hunts. This category also includes photography and video applications that record the GPS location tags for photos and videos or allow users to add location information to their photos.


	Scrabble, Tourality, iPhone Camera, Flickr, and Geocaching.


	

	

	

	

	5.4. 
	Citizen, Business
	Retail and Real Estate – Retail applications enable consumers to find the nearest store, provide in-store maps, check real-time inventory data, or shop from their phone, while real estate applications show houses for sale or rent or in foreclosure in a given area.
	Google Shopper, Target, Home Depot, HUD Homes, and Zillow Real Estate Search.
	

	

	

	

	5.5.
	Business
	Advertising – Location-based advertising allows users to receive ads relevant to their current location or based on patterns of frequently visited locations. The ads generally appear within other applications or in web browser windows.


	WHERE Ads, SkyHook, go2 Media, and Smaato.
	

	

	

	

	5.6.
	Citizen
	News and Weather – These applications provide users with weather and news targeted to their specific location. Some applications provide connection to local radio or TV providers for video or audio streaming, including access to police scanners.


	The Weather Channel, Weather HD, USA Today, NPR News, Stitcher Radio, ABC News, and Scanner911
	

	

	

	

	5.7.
	Citizen, Business, Industry
	Device Management – LBS management applications allow users to track and control their wireless devices from other sources (like a home computer) or to control other devices from their wireless devices. This may include tracking, locking, or erasing a lost phone, or locating, unlocking, and starting a vehicle.
	Find My iPhone, Lookout, OnStar MyLink, and myChevrolet.
	

	

	

	

	5.8.
	Government, e.g. Police, Citizen
	Public Safety – Some LBS applications principally serve public safety functions. In addition to the San Ramon Valley California Fire Protection District CPR application described above, Google is developing an “Amber Alert” application that would inform users in the possible vicinity of missing or abducted children. Another application that has been developed by the University of Maryland enables students to alert campus security to an incident, provide its location, and stream live audio and video directly to the dispatcher


	http://www.emergencymgmt.com/safety/Smartphone-Application-V911-Maryland.html


	

	

	

	6
	mHealth
	While People are living longer, many are not living  better. With soaring healthcare costs, and obesity and diabetes at epidemic levels, our nation’s physical and financial health is being compromised. To reverse these trends, healthcare providers need to find new ways to empower people to take charge of their health and lower costs without sacrificing quality. The question is: How do they bring about this transformation? The answer: technology. 
* Patients who stay connected with hospitals, caregivers and physicians are more satisfied with their care and get better quicker. They also have fewer repeat hospitalizations, manage their chronic disease better and cost payers/providers less money. Using innovative technology to securely connect  patients and families to physicians  and caregivers.
* Delivering quality Care in the field. Today’s healthcare professionals are highly mobile, visiting patients at their homes, clinics and hospitals, and they need immediate access to patient health and clinical reference information as well as to each other, to improve care.




	* Stay connected: Verizon is designing  solutions to keep patients connected with their healthcare
* Quality care in the Field: The Verizon mobile clinician solution is designed to leverage secure, high-speed mobile networks, smartphones and tablets, combined with partner solutions from providers such as IQMax, Calgary Scientific and CellTrak, to provide physicians and clinicians with the tools they need to be more productive and provide better care in the field.
	http://www.verizonenterprise.com/us/solutions/mobile-workforce/ 
	

	

	USA
		6.1. 
LifeWise mobile app 
	Collaboration with ensurances: 
Members who log into the mobile site can view claims, see their current plan benefit information and determine approximate treatment costs. Even if they don’t log in, users can still find a physician, shop for plans, locate the nearest urgent care center and contact customer service.members can locate nearby network physicians, urgent care clinics and emergency rooms.


	The LifeWise mobile app gives members convenient electronic access to services, including identification cards at the touch of a button. The app includes the ability to email the virtual card from their smartphone to their provider. The app’s other key components  include a provider directory and the  ability to connect to the insurer’s  customer service center and  24-hour nurse line.  Members with LifeWise personal  funding accounts can also use  the app to get account and balance information.


	https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/lifewise-mobile/id489751848?mt=8 
	

	iOS, Android, Windows Phone
	

		6.2.
OptumizeMe app
	The OptumizeMe app focuses on engaging consumers through gaming and socializing. In 2011, the app was released for Apple and Android devices. In March, it was updated to enable employers to conduct drawings and give prizes for employees meeting goals established in the app, a compliment to a feature already OptumizeMe that rewards users with virtual “badges” as goals are met.
	The app allows any user, even those who are not insured by United, to create or join a health or fitness challenge, such as walking or cycling, reducing stress and healthier eating. Users can track progress, invite others to join the challenge and communicate with other participants.
	https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.optumizeme.optum&hl=de 
	OptumHealth, a UnitedHeath Group company based in Golden Valley, Minn.
	

	

